Date of Birth: 20 May 1963<br/>
Birthplace: Bordeaux, France<br/>
Ordained as an apostle: 6 November 2025<br/>
<br/>
Born on May 20, 1963 in Bordeaux, France, Elder Caussé moved to Paris when he was 19. There he served one year of military service. He began dating Valérie Babin, who he had known since they were children. They were married on August 5, 1986, in the Bern Switzerland Temple, and they are the parents of five children. At the time of his call to the apostleship, he was in his 11th year of service as the Church’s Presiding Bishop. Elder Caussé also served as a counselor in the Presiding Bishopric (2012–2015) and a General Authority Seventy (2008–2012).